onymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert De Orway was born about 1098, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs Robert Orway. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1098–":"umbes 1098–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1123–Male":"1123–Surnud","1098–Male":"1098–Surnud","Abt 1098":"umbes 1098","Abt 1123":"umbes 1123","1123":"1123","1098":"1098","Orwey, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1098–":"noin 1098–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1123–Male":"1123–Kuollut","1098–Male":"1098–Kuollut","Abt 1098":"noin 1098","Abt 1123":"noin 1123","1123":"1123","1098":"1098","Orwey, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1098–":"environ 1098–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1123–Male":"1123–Décédé","1098–Male":"1098–Décédé","Abt 1098":"environ 1098","Abt 1123":"environ 1123","1123":"1123","1098":"1098","Orwey, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert De Orway est né environ 1098, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mrs Robert Orway. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1098–":"um 1098–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1123–Male